alarm-type.description: Ettp license not activated alarm - set when ettp license activation is disabled, cleared when ettp license activation is enabled
XCVR failed alarm - set when a xcvr is failed due to communication failure, cleared when the failure is recovered
XCVR unrecognized alarm - set when a xcvr is not on supported list, cleared when the xcvr is supported
XCVR high TX power alarm - set when TX power too high, cleared when TX power back to normal
XCVR high bias alarm - set when bias too high, cleared when bias back to normal
XCVR high RX power alarm - set when RX power too high, cleared when RX power back to normal
XCVR high voltage alarm - set when voltage too high, cleared when voltage back to normal
XCVR high temperature alarm - set when temperature too high, cleared when temperature back to normal
Link fault alarm - set when the link is down, cleared when the link is up
XCVR low TX power alarm - set when TX power too low, cleared when TX power back to normal
XCVR removed alarm - set when a xcvr is removed, cleared when the xcvr is inserted back
XCVR low RX power alarm - set when RX power too low, cleared when RX power back to normal
XCVR low bias alarm - set when bias too low, cleared when bias back to normal
XCVR low temperature alarm - set when temperature too low, cleared when temperature back to normal
XCVR low voltage alarm - set when voltage too low, cleared when voltage back to normal
Link capability mismatch alarm - set when configuration is incompatible with hardware, cleared when compatible
